main event: An unidentified flying object was observed traveling at a high rate of speed in a south-westerly direction for approximately 3 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on 30 November 1957,The observation involved radar and visual confirmation,The object was not identified as a shooting star but traveled under the moon,The observing party could not determine the object's height,The duration of the sighting was between 1-2 minutes.
sighted object: unidentified flying object traveling at high speed
